TY  - JOUR
T1  - Public vs. Private Offers in the Market for Lemons
AU  - Hörner, Johannes
AU  - Vieille, Nicolas
Y1  - 2009/01/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6917
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 29
EP  - 69
VL  - 77
IS  - 1
KW  - Bargaining
KW  - delay
KW  - impasse
KW  - observability
KW  - lemons problem
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6917
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study the role of observability in bargaining with correlated values. Short-run buyers sequentially submit offers to one seller. When previous offers are observable, bargaining is likely to end up in an impasse. In contrast, when offers are hidden, agreement is always reached, although with delay.
ER  - 

