mum risk, where the maximum is with respect to ?. There is a family of prior distributions for (δ, ?) that leads to a simple closed form for the integrated likelihood function. This integrated likelihood function coincides with the likelihood function for a normal, correlated random-effects model. Under random sampling, the corresponding quasi maximum likelihood estimator is consistent for ? as N?∞, with a standard limiting distribution. The limit results do not require normality or homoskedasticity (conditional on x) assumptions.
